{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, it is imperative to ascertain the advantages that healthcare providers can attain by incorporating CADx, a technical method of facilitating image interpretation.",
    "These systems contribute to the identification of medical images, patterns, and abnormalities by employing artificial intelligence and machine learning algorithms.",
    "The radiology, oncology, and pathology subspecialties are the most likely to implement the CADx systems, as diagnosing patients is essential for efficient patient management.",
    "The purpose of these is to facilitate decision-making or, at the very least, emphasize certain aspects that the initial diagnosis may have overlooked in order to guarantee the system's proper and efficient operation.",
    "We developed a dedicated CADx system, PolynetDWTCADx, for colorectal cancer (CRC) detection and segmentation."
  ]
}